HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 23
BY REPRESENTATIVES MCFARLAND, DEWITT, AND FIRMENT
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Katrice LaCour for his contributions in the Natchitoches
Parish showcase on the occasion of Natchitoches Day at the state capitol
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend Katrice LaCour for his contributions in the Natchitoches Parish showcase on
3 the occasion of Natchitoches Day at the state capitol.
4 WHEREAS, Katrice LaCour was born to Rainey and Nazy LaCour on March 13,
5 1966, in Chicago, Illinois; he attended Grambling State University and graduated in 1991
6 with a bachelor's degree in music education; his major instrument is the double bass and his
7 minor is the trumpet; and
8 WHEREAS, while in college, Mr. LaCour was an active member of the Grambling
9 State University Tiger Marching Band, Grambling Orchestra, Ruston Civic Symphony,
10 Grambling Jazz Ensemble, and Kappa Kappa Psi honorary band fraternity; as a member of
11 the Tiger Marching Band, he performed across the United States and Japan; and
12 WHEREAS, after completing his music education, Mr. LaCour served as the
13 orchestra and band director at Lakeview Junior and Senior High School in Campti,
14 Louisiana, during the 1991/1992 school year; throughout his teaching career, he has served
15 as a guest conductor, adjudicator, and clinician in numerous honor orchestras and festivals,
16 and his ensembles have participated in numerous Louisiana Music Educators Association
17 (LMEA) and national festivals since 1991; and
18 WHEREAS, Mr. LaCour currently serves as the orchestra director for the
19 Northwestern State University Elementary and Middle Laboratory Schools in Natchitoches,
20 Louisiana; in 2017, his middle school orchestra won gold in the high school division at
21 Festival Disney; in 2019, the orchestra performed at Carnegie Hall and for Governor John
